-- Goldman raises $6.5 bln for infrastructure fund
-- 
-- Thu Dec 28, 2006 7:17am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/28/businesspro-goldmansachs-infrastructure-idUSWEN162720061228

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Goldman Sachs Group Inc. ( GS.N ) said 
on Thursday it has raised more than $6.5 billion for a global 
infrastructure fund for investments in toll roads, airports and 
electric utilities. 

  The GS Infrastructure Partners fund will most likely focus 
on investments in Europe and North America. Goldman Sachs 
committed about $750 million of the fund's total capital.  Other investors included pension funds, insurance companies 
and banks, Goldman Sachs said.